longBusinessSummary: Red River Resources Limited, together with its subsidiaries, explores for and develops mineral projects in Australia. The company produces for copper, lead and zinc, gold, silver, and base metal, as well as precious metal deposits. It holds a 100% interest in the Thalanga project located in Queensland; and an interest in the Hillgrove project situated in Armidale, New South Wales. Red River Resources Limited was incorporated in 2002 and is based in Melbourne, Australia.
